main event: Weather station employees observed 4 oval-shaped objects moving at high speeds and hovering in the sky near Manchester, Tennessee.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be larger than commercial aircraft., Observers used binoculars and a telescope for a closer look., The objects were silver in color, without wings or tail surfaces., No sound was heard during the observation., The sighting was investigated by Air Force investigators, who suggested the objects could be weather balloons.
witness description: employees at an area weather station
